What do u mean by statistics?
- Statistics is the study and manipulation of data.
Statistics includes ways to gather, review, analyze, and draw conclusions from data.
Statistics can be used to make better-informed business and investing decisions.


What are the basic elements of Statistics?
- Population, Sample


Discrete variables and continuous variables are two types of
- quantitative classification	


Which one of the following variables is not categorical ?
- Age of a person


Which of the following statements are true?
I. All variables can be classified as quantitative or categorical variables. 
II. Categorical variables can be continuous variables. 
III. Quantitative variables can be discrete variables
- I and III


Match the following datatypes with their corresponding examples:
The following are the datatypes
a) Nominal				i) Ranking of users in a competition: The first, second, and third, etc.
b) Ordinal				ii) The amount of time required to complete a project.
c) Discrete				iii) The number of students in a class.
d) Continuous			iv) Gender (Women, Men)
- a: iv, b: i, c: iii, d: ii


Fifty bottles of water were randomly selected from a large collection of bottles in a company's warehouse. These fifty bottles are referred to as the
- Sample


Fifty bottles of water were randomly selected from a large collection of bottles in a company's warehouse. The large collection of bottles is referred to as the
- Population


A survey will be given to 100 students randomly selected from the class 10 students of DPS school. What is the population?
- All students in class 10


A survey will be given to 100 students randomly selected from the class 10 students of DPS school. What is the sample ?
- The 100 selected students


A mean is known as a statistic if it is computed from the -
- Sample


A medical researcher obtained blood specimens from a simple random sample (SRS)of 31 young children in New Delhi, all of whom were infected with malaria. What group of individuals is the most reasonable choice to serve as the population in this setting?
- all children in New Delhi, who have malaria
